<HEADLINE> Iran's Revolutionary Guards Launch War Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Revolutionary Guards Corps
(IRGC) on Sunday launched the main stage of Jerusalem military
exercise at Houweizeh, the southwestern Khuzestan province.
</P>
<P>
An IRGC command Brigadier General Rahim Noui-Aqdam said that
the troops equipped with heavy armors and tanks infiltrated the
territory of the hypothetical enemy, suppressed the enemy movement
and reached the targets.
</P>
<P>
He said that modern armors, tanks, personnel-carriers and
parachutists brought at the theater carried out the main stage of
the exercise, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Noui-Aqdam said the Iranian forces carried reconnaissance
missions and clean-up operation against the hypothetical enemy's
chemical attack as well as firing anti-aircraft machine guns.
</P>
<P>
He said that columns of the infantry and armored troops are
scheduled to move toward the border city of Khorramshahr on
Monday to mark the anniversary of the liberation of the strategic
city in 1982.
</P>
<P>
The commander noted that the military exercises were being held
to commemorate those killed in the operation to liberate
Khorramshahr from the Iraqi forces and to boost the preparedness
of the IRGC troops.
</P>
<P>
He said that the exercises were being held in an area of 250
square kilometers in three stages. However, he did not mention how
many troops were involved in the maneuver. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
