clearing landmines, is among the products he would be punting in
Libya, where thousands of landmines planted during the second
world war posed a serious problem.
</P>
<P>
Libya was in any event not that interested in acquiring arms,
he said.
</P>
<P>
The delegation led by Trade and Industry Minister Alec Erwin
includes a number of the country's leading businessmen who are
hoping to secure contracts worth billions of U.S. dollars which
are up for grabs since the suspension of U.N. sanctions against
Libya.
</P>
