This follows Libya's hand-over of two men suspected of the 1988
bombing of a Pan American flight over Lockerbie in Scotland for
trial in the Netherlands, a settlement which South Africa helped
broker.
</P>
<P>
Libya has revealed plans to invest considerable sums of money
in water supply and transport projects, but analysts were unaware
of it being in the market for significant quantities of new arms.
</P>
<P>
Denel comprised 22 companies which sold a wide range of other
high-tech equipment, including soya bean products, plastics, money
counters and information technology, said Sisulu. 
