<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Registers 3,271 Overseas-funded Enterprises in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- A total of 3,271 overseas-funded
enterprises were registered in the first quarter of this year,
down 16.9 percent from the same period last year, according to the
State Administration for Industry and Commerce (SAIC).
</P>
<P>
Investment of these enterprises is valued at 13.23 billion U.S.
dollars, down 13.3 percent, and total registered capital was 6.77
billion dollars, a decrease of 11.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The real estate industry, however, saw substantial growth in
all the above-mentioned indexes.
</P>
<P>
Newly registered overseas enterprises involved in mining,
catering,education,as well as radio, film and TV experienced a
year-on-year decrease. However, all other indexes were up from the
year-ago period, according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
Sources also indicate that growth of overseas-funded
enterprises slowed by 22 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
The total investment of joint ventures increased in the first
three months, but other indexes declined compared with the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
The registered capital of overseas enterprises in primary
industries, and the capital scribed by foreign investors in these
industries were up, while the corresponding indexes of secondary
and tertiary industries were down from same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Newly registered enterprises funded by Oceanic and African
countries increased and the capital subscribed by those countries
rose as well. However, the number of new enterprises funded by
European investors decreased, but their capital subscriptions saw
some growth.
</P>
<P>
Both the number of new enterprises and capital subscriptions
provided by Asian and North and South American investors were less
than in the first quarter of 1998.
</P>
<P>
By the end of March, a total of 228,300 overseas-funded
enterprises were registered in China, with 782.2 billion U.S.
dollars of investment, including total registered capital of 471.1
billion dollars. The registered capital subscribed by foreign
investors amounted to 317.3 billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
