<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Top Lawmaker Stresses Supervision (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Carrying out supervision on governments, courts and
procuratorates is a power granted to the people's congresses and
their standing committees by the Chinese Constitution. Meanwhile,
the Constitution also stipulates that the people's congresses must
carry out supervision under the leadership of the Party," said Li.
</P>
<P>
The Party has led the people to enact and implement the
Constitution and other laws, and it's also necessary for the Party
to carry out its own activities within the restraints of the
Constitution and other laws, he added.
</P>
<P>
"The ultimate purpose of the people's congresses' supervisory
work is to promote lawful administration and judicial justice.
Therefore, it's in fact a kind of support to the work of the
government and the judicial bodies," Li stressed.
</P>
<P>
While explaining the draft regulations on judicial supervision,
Li said that the supervisory power must not be exercised by any
individual lawmakers, but only by the people's congress and its
standing committee as a collective power.
</P>
<P>
"Meanwhile, it's also impossible for the people's congresses to
probe into too many judicial cases," noted Li. "Therefore, we must
focus on those individual cases which have aroused strong
criticism and a lot of complaints."
</P>
<P>
He also reminded people's congresses at all levels of the
importance of respecting the judicial organs' power and right to
handle judicial cases with full independence.
</P>
<P>
"The people's congress should never get involved in the
specific process of the handling of a judicial case," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Li also studied the latest development of the reform of state-
owned enterprises in Shandong and the local "Vegetable Basket"
project, which aims at guaranteeing ample vegetable supply for the
urban residents.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
