<HEADLINE> Chi Haotian Meets Russian Navy Chief (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister General
Chi Haotian met here this afternoon with Commander-in-Chief of the
Russian navy Vladimir Kuroyedov and exchanged views on cooperation
and exchanges between the navies of the two countries, bilateral
relations,and international and regional issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Chi, who is also vice-chairman of China's Central Military
Commission and a state councilor,said the Sino-Russian strategic
partnership of coordination has been enriched and deepened.
</P>
<P>
He said that bilateral military relations are an important
component of the overall relations between the two countries,
adding that China hopes to further enhance cooperation with Russia
in the fields of defense and the armed forces, including naval
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
On the international situation, Chi said that peace and
development are still the mainstream of the times, and the trend
toward multipolarity is irresistible.
</P>
</TEXT>
