<HEADLINE> Shanghai, Houston: Hi-Tech Partnership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai,China's largest city,and
Houston of the United States signed a letter of intention here
this evening for the creation of a cooperative partnership between
the two cities to develop high technologies.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Mayor Xu Kuangdi and Houston Chief Executive Albert
Haines participated in the signing ceremony in the municipal
government building in downtown Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the Shanghai Municipal Government said the two
cities, both leading industrial bases and world-renowned
metropolises, both intend to play a significant role in their
countries' technological innovation.
</P>
<P>
Along with cooperation in the field of hi-tech, the two cities
will also try to develop solid commercial and economic ties to
meet the global challenges of the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Shanghai, Haines visited Shanghai Airlines
and a hi-tech company in the Pudong New Development Area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
