<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Urges NATO to Stop Bombing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen
reiterated today that the U.S.-led NATO must stop its wanton and
indiscriminate bombing of Yugoslavia immediately in order to bring
the Kosovo crisis back to political settlement.
</P>
<P>
Qian made the remarks while meeting with Greek Foreign Minister
George Papandreou. He said that the NATO attack on Chinese embassy
in Yugoslavia touched off the strong indignation of the Chinese
people, and that the U.S.-led NATO must conduct a comprehensive,
thorough and fair investigation, and make the truth public, and it
should be held fully responsible for that.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that China and Greece are both countries with a long
history, and that the two countries can approach issues from a
long-term perspective, adding that the Kosovo issue, a complicated
one which is connected with different ethnic groups and religions,
can only be settled politically.
</P>
<P>
Qian expressed his appreciation for Greece's efforts to seek a
political settlement of the Kosovo issue.
</P>
<P>
Papandreou, who arrived here Sunday for a two-day working visit
to China, briefed Qian on Greece's position on the Kosovo issue.
He said that military actions can only trigger various kinds of
contradictions instead of solving this complicated matter.
</P>
<P>
He said that Greece, as a country in Balkan, will make its
effort to let relevant countries and ethnic groups in the region
live in harmony.
</P>
<P>
The Greek foreign minister added that Greece is fully prepared
to increase consultations and cooperation with China, in order to
seek a political solution of the crisis.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also spoke highly of the smooth development of
the Sino-Greek relations in recent years. They agreed that the two
governments will work together to promote mutually beneficial
cooperation in a variety of areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
