<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> COMESA Summit Opens in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The fourth summit of the Common
Market of Eastern and Southern Africa (COMESA) opened here Monday
in Kenyan capital Nairobi in a bid to pave the way for a COMESA
free trade area.
</P>
<P>
The meeting has drawn a dozen heads of state and government,
namely presidents from Kenya, Burundi, Djibouti, Zimbabwe, the
Democratic Republic of Congo, Rwanda, Namibia, Malawi, Sudan,
Tanzania, Uganda and Zambia.
</P>
<P>
The opening ceremony started with the playing of the national
anthem of Kenya, and the COMESA song expressing the unity for
freedom in trade in COMESA region.
</P>
<P>
In his welcoming speech, Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi said,
"despite the challenges we have faced, we have remained steadfast
in our common resolve to transform COMESA into a free trade area."
</P>
<P>
He said, together under the umbrella of COMESA, "we must work
for freedom in trade, that will enable us participate effectively
and gain from the global economy."
</P>
<P>
Moi urged all COMESA member countries to be united in pursuing
issues of concern, saying "the solution to Africa's problems must
come from Africans themselves."
</P>
<P>
In his keynote address, President Frederick Chiluba of Zambia
who has served as Chairman of the Comesa Authority over the past
two years, noted that greater integration and cooperation within
COMESA could serve as an effective cushion against the adverse
effects of globalization.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the free trade area, Chiluba said, "we have
pursued the goal of creating a common market where goods,
services, labor and capital are free to move across our borders."
He added that "we set ourselves the goal of attaining a free trade
area by October 31, 2000."
</P>
<P>
"We reaffirmed our commitment to achieving this goal, and to
establish a common external tariff by the year 2004," he said,
noting that the rate of intra-COMESA trade is growing at a
healthy 20 percent per annum.
</P>
<P>
He told the participants that to the goal of a common external
tariff, " I feel comfortable to inform you that a firm foundation
is already being laid for its smooth introduction and operation."
</P>
<P>
Chiluba also highlighted the progress in the implementation of
programs and projects discussed at the last COMESA summit related
to telecommunications, African Guarantee Facility, free movement
of people, investment promotion, private sector development and
the COMESA court of justice.
</P>
<P>
Zambian President Sam Nujoma and his Djibouti counterpart
Ismail Omar Guelleh spoke highly of Chiluba's contributions to
COMESA during his two- year term as chairman of the COMESA
authority.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day summit, the heads of state and government of
the COMESA members will consider the report presented by the 7th
Meeting of the Minister Council on such issues as trade and
customs, monetary and financial cooperation as well as
infrastructure development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
