<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial Stresses Economic Development (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The People's Daily, China's leading
newspaper, echoes Chinese President Jiang Zemin's call on the
whole country to focus on economic development after the NATO
missile attack on the Chinese embassy in Belgrade in an editorial
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"After learning the atrocities of the U.S.-led NATO, the
Chinese people not only felt great indignation, but also
recognized the utmost importance of improving China's economic
power and comprehensive national strength as quickly as possible,"
says the editorial entitled "Unswervingly adhere to taking
economic development as the central task."
</P>
<P>
The editorial says that a major factor behind hegemonism and
power politics lies in the fact that they have powerful economic
strength and mighty military power backed by their economic
strength.
</P>
<P>
The editorial recalls that in his keynote speech at the meeting
welcoming Chinese personnel back from Yugoslavia, President Jiang
said: "We will continue to unswervingly adhere to taking economic
development as our central task."
</P>
<P>
"This has precisely reflected the Chinese people's
determination to turn grief into strength and make every effort to
develop China into a socialist power," the editorial adds.
</P>
<P>
The editorial says that the shift from stressing class struggle
to taking economic development as the central task some 20 years
ago represents a significant revision of its guiding ideology and
political line by the Communist Party of China.
</P>
</TEXT>
