<HEADLINE> China, Greece Seek Political Solution to Kosovo Issue (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Both China and Greece have vowed
to seek a political solution to the Kosovo issue, as expressed by
their foreign ministers in talks here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan exchanged views on the
Kosovo crisis with his Greek counterpart,George Papandreou,who
is on a working visit to China.
</P>
<P>
Briefing Tang on Greece's position on the Kosovo issue and its
efforts at diplomatic mediation, Papandreou said Greece, a Balkan
nation, is dedicated to the peaceful co-existence of all nations
and ethic groups in the region.
</P>
<P>
Greece will not take part in NATO military action, but instead
will promote a political solution to the crisis, grant
humanitarian aid to all parties,and appeal for post-war
construction, he pledged.
</P>
<P>
Greece is ready to urge a NATO bombing pause and a return to
the United Nation's effort for a political solution, he pointed
out.
</P>
<P>
He said Greece places importance on China's role, and is
willing to enhance consultation and coordination with the Chinese
side.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated his regret over NATO's attack on the Chinese
embassy in Yugoslavia, and once again expressed condolences for
the death of the three Chinese journalists.
</P>
<P>
Tang said China appreciates Greece's refusal to join NATO's
military action and its efforts toward a political solution,
adding that China supports their positive mediation.
</P>
</TEXT>
