<HEADLINE> 1 Soldier Killed, 26 Injured in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- One Turkish soldier was killed and
26 others wounded in a terrorist attack in southeastern Turkey
late Sunday night, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that a group of rebels of the outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK) launched a rocket attack on the Turkish
security forces in Semdili town of Hakkari province, causing the
casualties.
</P>
<P>
The injured were rushed to hospitals in Van and Hakkari
provinces, among whom 10 seriously injured were taken to Ankara
for treatment later.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting since 1984 for an independent
Kurdish state in southeastern Turkey. Conflicts between the
Turkish government and the PKK have claimed over 37,000 lives.
</P>
<P>
PKK leader Abdullah Ocalan was captured by Turkish special
agents in Kenya in mid-February and has been detained on
Imrali Island in Marmara Sea near Turkey's western province of
Bursa for trials on charges of treason. 
</P>
