<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets With Chief Executive of Macao SAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin met
here today with Edmund Ho Hau Wah, the first chief executive of
the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR), which will be
established after Macao returns to China on December 20 this year.
</P>
<P>
"In the over 400 years of Portuguese rule over Macao, all
successive Macao governors were directly appointed and sent in by
the Portuguese government. You're the first Chinese to serve as
Macao's chief executive," noted Jiang after congratulating Ho on
his election.
</P>
<P>
The election of Ho by a selection committee, whose members are
all permanent residents of Macao, through secret ballot reflects
the Chinese central government's firm determination to implement
the principles of "one country, two systems" and "Macao people
running Macao, and has also opened a new era in the history of
Macao, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
"'One country, two systems' is a state policy China will long
pursue, and after the founding of the Macao SAR, we will strictly
follow the stipulations of the SAR's Basic Law and will never
interfere with any affairs within the scope of the SAR's self-
government," said the president.
</P>
<P>
He also pledged that the central government will give all-out
support to Ho if he encounters problems and needs assistance.
</P>
<P>
As the first chief executive, Jiang said, Ho shoulders the
great historic mission of leading all Macao residents in putting
the principle of "one country, two systems" into practice, and
thus faces an arduous task.
</P>
<P>
"I hope you will live up to the great expectations of the
entire Chinese people, including the 400,000-strong Macao
residents," said Jiang. "And I believe that Macao will have a
better tomorrow."
</P>
<P>
Ho replied that he will try his best to make due contributions
to Macao's stability and further development, as well as to the
prosperity of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Vice Premier Qian Qichen and several other officials also were
present during the meeting. 
</P>
