<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Senior Pakistani Officer (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin met
with Pervez Musharaf, chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff
Committee and chief of Army Staff of Pakistan, here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also chairman of China's Central Military
Commission, said that China and Pakistan are neighbors with a
traditional friendship.
</P>
<P>
"During the long period of friendly exchanges, the peoples of
our two countries comprehend and sympathize with each other," he
said, adding that China appreciates Pakistan's firm support and
assistance in such issues as Taiwan, Tibet and human rights.
</P>
<P>
According to Jiang, U.S.-led NATO wantonly bombed the sovereign
state Yugoslavia in total disregard of the U.N. Charter and
relevant international laws and agreements. "The Chinese
government and people expressed their strong opposition to such an
action from the very beginning," he said.
</P>
<P>
Not long ago, Jiang said, U.S.-led NATO went so far as to
attack the Chinese embassy in Yugoslavia with missiles. The
president said that attack constituted "the gross violation of
Chinese sovereignty and wanton trampling of international laws and
relevant international agreements."
</P>
<P>
The only way to tackle the Kosovo crisis, the president pointed
out, is that NATO stops bombing. "No political solution can be
discussed otherwise," he added.
</P>
<P>
On the regional situation, Jiang said that the South Asian
subcontinent constitutes a major component of Asia. "Without the
stability or development in South Asia, there would be no peace or
prosperity in the whole of Asia," he said, adding that China
sincerely hopes that the subcontinent maintains peace and
stability.
</P>
