<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Host Meeting on Parliamentary Committee System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- A conference on parliamentary
committee systems, organized by the Institute of Parliamentary
Studies of the Bangladesh Parliament, will be held here on May
27-28, a press release of the Parliament Secretariat said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The conference will focus on issues related to the committee
system in Bangladesh, covering such issues as oversight of the
government, the role of women within the committees, the role of
the committee chairpersons, and the role of the committees in
budget procedures.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be inaugurated by Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina, and the closing ceremony will be addressed by Khaleda Zia,
leader of the opposition in parliament.
</P>
<P>
Speakers from India and Britain will present papers at the
conference about the committee systems of parliament in their
respective countries, and an international parliamentary expert
from the United Nations Development Program will deliver a speech
on the comparative constitutional law.
</P>
<P>
Some 400 people are expected to participate in the conference,
which is targeted at members and senior officials of the
Secretariat of the Bangladesh Parliament. 
</P>
