<HEADLINE> Share Prices Drop on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Share prices slid significantly
on Singapore Stock Market Monday as gains lasted briefly because
of spreading cautious sentiment to the market.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index dropped 20.50 points to end
at 1,932.80.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover came to 1,168.64 million shares valued at
1,071.35 million Singapore dollars (621.97 million U.S. dollars).
Declines outnumbered advances by 100 to 31 with 108 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Comport topped the most actives chart with a volume of 35.42
million shares. Popular was the second most heavily traded stock
with 31.63 million shares done. Summit was the next with 30.96
million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
GE Life was the biggest gainer of the day soaring by 220 cents
to close at 23.20 Singapore dollars. It was followed by TIBS w00
that registered a 123-cent rise and finished at 3.10 Singapore
dollars. TIBS 500 ran up 86 cents to end at 4.14 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
SIA F led losers of the day shedding 60 cents to close at 15.40
Singapore dollars. SPH, SPH 100 and Seaview sank 50 cents each to
end at 25.00, 24.70 and 10.00 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market opened with a strong note but it
weakened in later trading as institutional players took a cautious
approach to the market while retail players punted the market.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said reported comments from Finance Minister Richard Hu
advising caution following the U.S. move towards a tightening bias
in its monetary policy had dampened sentiment.
</P>
<P>
They noted that most of the actively-traded stocks were penny
stocks, with retail players spurred by rumors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
