<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Meets with Chief Executive of Macao SAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji said
today that the appointment of the first Chief Executive of the
Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR), Edmund Ho Hau Wah,
marks "a new page in the history of Macao".
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu made the remark in a meeting with Edmund Ho Hau Wah
here this afternoon. He said the successful election of the first
Chief Executive not only fully reflected the principle of fairness,
justice, transparency, democracy and honesty, but also represented
the common aspiration of Macao residents and the central
government's determination to implement the policy of "one country,
two systems" and "Macao people governing Macao".
</P>
<P>
Zhu expressed great expectations to the first government of the
Macao SAR, which will be established on December 20 this year, as
well as firm confidence in economic development and social
stability of Macao after its return to the motherland. He also
emphasized that the central government will fully support the
Chief Executive of the Macao SAR in his work.
</P>
<P>
Ho Hau Wah said he felt greatly honored by his appointment by
the central government, and he will work hard for long-term
stability and development of Macao.
</P>
<P>
Before the meeting, State Councillor and Secretary-General of
the State Council Wang Zhongyu announced decree No. 264 appointing
Edmund Ho Hau Wah the first Chief Executive of the Macao SAR. On
behalf of the State Council, Premier Zhu granted the official
certificate of appointment to Ho Hau Wah.
</P>
<P>
Attending the meeting and the appointing ceremony were Vice-
Premier Qian Qichen, and Liao Hui, director for the Hong Kong and
Macao Affairs Office of the State Council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
