<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan Urged to Follow Path of Peaceful Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- China today urged Japan to honor
its solemn commitments of not becoming a military power and of
following the path of peaceful development.
</P>
<P>
When commenting on the approval of the new Japan-U.S. defense
cooperation guidelines today by Japan's House of Councillors,
Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao said here today that China
is gravely concerned about Japan's act of going against the
historical trend and its insistence on strengthening Japan-U.S.
military cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that Japan should honor its solemn commitments of not
becoming a military power and of following the path of peaceful
development through its real action, properly approach the Taiwan
issue strictly in accordance with relevant principles, and not do
anything interfering in China's internal affairs or undermining
Sino-Japanese relations. Only when Japan does so, will it help
reduce doubts and uneasiness of China and other neighboring
countries and safeguard the regional peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has repeatedly urged Japan to act
prudently, and Japan has made some commitments and explained its
stance to China in this regard, Zhu said, adding that "We will
listen to what the Japanese side says and watch what it does."
</P>
</TEXT>
