<HEADLINE> Romanian PM Visits Moldova </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Prime Minister Radu
Vasile on Monday started his two-day official visit to Moldova.
</P>
<P>
The visit is "important" as the Romanian government attaches
special importance to its "privileged relations" with Moldova,
Vasile said.
</P>
<P>
The two countries should support each other in the process of
European economic integration, he added.
</P>
<P>
Vasile is expected to meet with his Moldovian counterpart Ion
Sturza to discuss issues in the fields of economy, finance and
customs.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian prime minister will also hold talks with Moldovian
President Petru Lucinschi and parliament President Dumitru Diacov.
</P>
<P>
Romania and Moldova have signed 40 agreements since the two
countries established diplomatic relations on August 29, 1991,
when the Republic of Moldova was proclaimed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
