<HEADLINE> Northwestern Chinese Private Hi-Tech Company Offering A Shares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The Xi'an Seastar Modern-Tech Co.
Ltd., a major computer and network products producer in Shaanxi
Province, will be offering 68 million A shares with a face value
of 4.68 yuan through the Shanghai Stock Exchange on Wednesday,
according to media reports.
</P>
<P>
The company expects to raise 318.24 million yuan from the sale
of the shares. It will spend the money on three new computer
production lines that will boost annual production to 700,000 sets
in three years, and other projects, according to a prospectus.
</P>
<P>
The company will also build a notebook computer production line
with an annual output of 15,000 sets, as well as a PCTV production
line of machines that function both as a personal computer and a
television set.
</P>
<P>
It will build the largest software development center in
northwestern China of software for commercial information analysis
systems, commercial management, education, and entertainment.
</P>
<P>
The new company will be owned by the Xi'an Seastar Technology (
Group) Company, a private company based in Xi'an, the capital of
Shaanxi Province, which was started in 1992 with registered
capital of 30,000 yuan. It has by now expanded into computers,
supermarkets, beverages, real estate, and modern agriculture. In
1995, it ranked 28th among the top 100 high-tech companies in
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
