<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Hosts Event for Tax Free Asia Pacific 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 24 (Xinhua) -- A five-day event, Tax Free Asia
Pacific 1999 (TFAP), the fifth of its kind, was launched at the
Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center Monday with a view to
looking into the future prospects of the region for the tax free
industry.
</P>
<P>
The event includes an exhibition and a conference entitled "
Planting the Seeds of Recovery" as well as a series of dynamic
workshops.
</P>
<P>
About 200 exhibitors from around the globe feature a
comprehensive display of premium duty- and tax-free goods
including liquor, tobacco, fragrance, cosmetics, accessories,
jewelry, gifts and confectionery.
</P>
<P>
Jean-Marie Cerruti, president of the Tax Free World Association,
said at the opening of the conference that the Asia Pacific region,
with its vast population and active travel industry, represents
the greatest potential worldwide for the travel and retail
industry.
</P>
<P>
Last year duty- and tax-free sales reached a retail value of 20.
5 billion U.S. dollars with Asia Pacific contributing 20 percent
to that figure.
</P>
<P>
Despite the economic downturn, he said, "We are confident that
the TFAP will benefit from a large range of internationally known
brands, offering an incomparable multi-product platform in a
unique environment, with the best possible conditions to meet and
do business."
</P>
<P>
Stephen Ip, HK Secretary for Economic Services, described the
international duty and tax free industry as dynamic.
</P>
<P>
He said the industry enables consumers traveling between
different countries and regions to purchase high quality luxury
merchandise at attractive prices.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the sales of tax-free commodities in Hong Kong took up
some 10 percent of the total market share in the Asia Pacific
region.
</P>
<P>
Last year when the exhibition was first held in Hong Kong, it
recorded an overwhelming success featuring more than 300
international brands from over 20 countries.
</P>
<P>
It also attracted over 2,000 quality trade buyers from the Asia
Pacific region notwithstanding the region-wide financial turmoil
and economic downturn.
</P>
<P>
This testifies to the importance attached to this industry-wide
event, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ip expressed the belief that this year's exhibition is going to
break new ground. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
