</P>
<P>
-- In two months of operation in Kosovo, NATO said it has
destroyed one third of the heavy armaments and about 100 planes of
the Yugoslav forces with 14,000 bombs. NATO also announced the
reinforcement of its ground deployment in the Balkans in
preparation for a deployment in Kosovo once a political solution
is found.
</P>
<P>
-- The Italian government suspects that the order to
assassinate a senior government advisor on labor issues was given
by someone close to the leadership of labor unions. Massimo
D'Antona, who was assassinated last week by the terrorist group "
Red Brigade", helped the government conclude talks on a social
pact with the unions last December. 
</P>
