<HEADLINE> EDS-Details Added Chinese President Meets Jamaican Governor-general </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin met
with Howard Cooke, governor-general of Jamaica, and his wife at
the Diaoyutai State Guesthouse here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Extending welcome to Cooke and his party, Jiang praised Cooke's
contribution to promoting the growth of bilateral ties between
China and Jamaica and expressed his appreciation for the Jamaican
government's adherence to the "One China" policy and refusal to
develop official relations with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
As developing countries, Jiang said, China and Jamaica now face
the common tasks of developing domestic economies, improving
people's living standards and safeguarding world peace.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the principle of treating each other equally,
mutual support and enhancing exchanges and friendship, the Chinese
government is willing to make concerted efforts with the Jamaican
government to bring the Chinese-Jamaican relationship featuring
long-term stability and sustainable growth into the 21st century,
the Chinese president said.
</P>
<P>
Cooke, who is also the sponsor of Jamaica-China Friendship
Association, said that the Chinese people are diligent and
intelligent. China is an important country in the world, with
its stability and development playing a pivotal role in the
world's stability and development.
</P>
<P>
Cooke told Jiang that he had paid close attention to China's
economic construction and development for years. He expressed his
admiration for China's achievements, in particular its success in
feeding and clothing its 1.2 billion people.
</P>
<P>
Cooke and his party are here as guests of the Chinese People's
Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC). CPAFFC
President Qi Huaiyuan was present at the meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
