<HEADLINE> Performances of Arts Academies Begin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The week-long performance of
Chinese arts academies began last night with the dance show by the
Beijing Institute of Dancing at the Century Theater.
</P>
<P>
Yang Ying, an outstanding young dancer, Yu Xiaoxue and Liu Zhen,
both top national dance award winners, performed for the public in
the first event organized by the Ministry of Culture.
</P>
<P>
The prize-winning dance performances about Qinshihuang, China's
first emperor, and the Yellow River, were well received by the
audience.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, the institute provided the dance lovers with a
delicate performance adapted from the well-known Chinese drama of
Thunderstorm written by Cao Yu.
</P>
<P>
Western-styled ballet also became favorite of Chinese audience.
Wang Qimin, who won the title for a international ballet
competition in Paris, and Li Jun performed in the classic show of
Swan Lake.
</P>
<P>
To mark the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People's
Republic of China, the ministry specially organized the
performances, including dance and drama symphony.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 best members of 13 prominent arts academies
participated in the performance from May 23 to 28.  
</P>
</TEXT>
