<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Residents Show Strong Environmental Awareness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- A recent telephone survey by the
Beijing Business Consultation Corporation of 250 Beijing residents
shows that Beijing residents have a strong environmental
protection awareness.
</P>
<P>
Almost all the respondents cited environment as one of three
important factors affecting the living quality. Nearly 71 percent
showed willingness to bear some environmental protection expenses,
and 21.5 percent said it depends.
</P>
<P>
The survey also indicates that nearly 88 percent of the
respondents are ready to use cloth bags instead of plastic bags to
reduce "white pollution".
</P>
<P>
Although many environment-friendly products are higher-priced
than ordinary products, 64 percent of the respondents expressed
their willingness to buy environment-friendly products. Only less
than five percent said they would definitely not buy such products.
</P>
<P>
In addition, more than a half of the respondents have used one
or two types of environment-friendly or "green" products, and 12.3
percent have used more than three types of "green" products,
according to the survey.
</P>
<P>
People below the age of 40 are more enthusiastic in using
environment-friendly products than those aged above 40, the survey
shows.
</P>
<P>
More than 92 percent of the respondents said they support and
will participate in classified collection of garbage. Only 0.4
percent said they would definitely not support or take part in the
activity, according to the survey.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
