<HEADLINE> Spurs Advances to Western Final, Jazz on Brink of Elimination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Tim Duncan had 33 points and 14
rebounds as the San Antonio Spurs beat the Los Angeles Lakers 118-
107 away and advanced to the Western Conference final with four
wins of the best-of-seven series.
</P>
<P>
Duncan, a strong MVP candidate, shot 11-of-14 from both the
field and the line in the match. Jaren Jackson had 20 points while
Avery Johnson added 19 and 10 assists.
</P>
<P>
Shaquille O'Neal had a big game for the Lakers with 36 points
and 14 rebounds, but he could not save his team from elimination.
</P>
<P>
In Portland, Isaiah Rider scored seven of his game-high 24
points in the final 30 seconds as the Trail Blazers pushed the two-
time defending Western Conference champion Utah Jazz to the brink
with an 81-75 victory.
</P>
<P>
After dropping the first game of the best-of-seven series,
Portland has won the next three and can wrap up their upset with a
win at Utah on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Karl Malone and Byron Russell scored 17 each for Utah. 
</P>
</TEXT>
