<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila Reminds Oil Firms of Social Responsibility </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government Monday
reminded oil firms of their responsibility to the public as it
questioned their decision to impose another round of oil price
increases in the country.
</P>
<P>
Executive Secretary Ronaldo Zamora branded as inconsiderate the
reported plan of some big oil companies to impose another round of
oil price hikes.
</P>
<P>
"They should understand that they have a responsibility to the
public and not just their shareholders," Zamora said in a radio
interview.
</P>
<P>
He also said the move of these oil companies may prompt some
people to hoard oil products.
</P>
<P>
But he said the government is not likely to get back into the
business of controlling oil prices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
