<HEADLINE> New Zoo Being Built in Northeastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The city of Shenyang, capital of
China's Liaoning Province, will get a new 200-hectare zoo for
animals from areas with cold climates.
</P>
<P>
The zoo is situated in the Huishan Mountain scenic area about
40 kilometers from downtown Shenyang and is expected to be home to
150 species of wild animals.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of construction work on the habitat has started
at an estimated cost of 200 million yuan, with about 120 million
being allocated for this year. It is expected to be completed in
two years and will partly go into trial operation this year and
open to the public on June 1 next year.
</P>
<P>
It will have five areas: a habitat for wild animals, a man-made
lake, a walking area for visitors, a park, and a food service area.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
