<HEADLINE> More Foreign Investment in Southern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province, used 1.2 billion U.S. dollars of
overseas investment in the first four months this year, an
increase of 8.9 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The city's statistics bureau said that the growth trend was in
sharp contrast to the first quarter, when foreign investment saw a
decline. The city had the second largest amount of foreign
investment in any Chinese city.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou exported 2.6 billion U.S. dollars worth of goods in
the four-month period, down 10.5 percent year on year, and
imported 2.6 billion U.S. dollar worth, an increase of 20.6
percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
