<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, May 24 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share market
closed higher Monday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index was 8 points higher at 2,157 with a turnover
of 134 million NZ dollars (72.7 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the leading stocks, Telecom put on 8 cents to 830 cents,
Baycorp Holdings gained 6 cents to 525, both Auckland Airport and
Sky Network rose by 5 cents to 287 and 310 cents respectively, and
Air New Zealand-A collected 2 cents to 292.
</P>
<P>
Fletcher stocks closed lower with Energy falling 7 cents to 433
 cents, Building 6 to 304 cents and Paper 2 to 146 cents.
</P>
<P>
Contact Energy lost 3 cents to 352 cents and Carter Holt Harvey
1 to 232 cents. 
