<HEADLINE> Bomb Blast Kills 9 in Eastern Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 24 (Xinhua) -- A bomb explosion rocked the
peaceful College Road area of Daska city in eastern Pakistan at
about 08:45 a.m. local time (0345 GMT) Monday, killing nine people
and injuring 35 others.
</P>
<P>
According to reports, the explosion occurred at the laborer
market, where local laborers had as usual gathered in search of
work.
</P>
<P>
Five persons were reported killed on the spot, while four
succumbed to injuries a little later at the Civil Hospital, Daska.
 Among the 35 others who were injured in the blast, the condition
of at least 10 is stated to be critical.
</P>
<P>
The bomb was reportedly placed in a polythene bag and slung on
one of the cycles parked in the vicinity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
