<HEADLINE> First Chinese Movie On Oroqen Culture to Be Released </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, May 24 (Xinhua) -- China has finished filming its
first movie on the Oroqen, an ethnic group living in the Northeast,
as part of the 50th anniversary celebrations of the new China.
</P>
<P>
The movie, "Tribe of Hawks", is based on the historic discovery
by the Chinese government of this last primitive society and how
it improved the lives of the minority by bringing them into
socialist society. It portrays the nomadic hunting lives of the
tribe and a touching love story.
</P>
<P>
The population of the Oroqen now numbers 10,000, most of whom
are living in Inner Mongolia and Heilongjiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Wang Gengnian, deputy director of State Radio, Film, and
Television Administration, said that only the Chinese government
could put so much effort into looking for the last tribe and that
only China could spend millions of yuan on a film on a small
ethnic tribe, he says. 
</P>
