<HEADLINE> Tamil Rebels Target Sri Lanka's Capital Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Tamil rebels of
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) have once again targeted
the country's capital city Colombo, police sources said Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to military intelligence a lorry loaded with
explosives had left for Colombo from Vavuniya in North Central
province with six tiger cadres to attack a prime target.
</P>
<P>
All police stations and military units in and around Colombo
have been placed on full alert since last Saturday to look out for
the lorry.
</P>
<P>
Security at key government installations has also been
tightened.
</P>
<P>
Two LTTE suspects who had been arrested at Vavuniya last week
had revealed details of the planned attack on Colombo.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, Colombo was hit by a wave of bomb attacks.
Police suspected that the Tamil rebels had sent bomb squads to
disrupt civilian life.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a separatist war against the Sri
Lankan government since 1983 for a Tamil homeland in the north and
east of the country. 
