since January 19 until mid-May have left at least 350 dead and
some 6,000 houses burnt down.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the number of people leaving Indonesia
from Soekarno Hatta International Airport here has increased in
recent weeks. About 350,000 people went abroad from the airport in
April, while the figure is likely to reach 400,000 this month.
</P>
<P>
The people leaving the country amid fears that unrest could
erupt during the ongoing general election campaign, the reports
said.
</P>
