<HEADLINE> Time Is Ripe for Consumer Credit in China: Banker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- A People's Bank of China official
said today that China has all the necessary conditions to develop
the consumer credit business.
</P>
<P>
Huang Jiaquan, of the central bank's monetary department, said
that most urban Chinese consumers are now turning their attention
to more costly consuming items and that consumer credit has become
a necessity to bridge the gap between income and expenditure.
</P>
<P>
Although the number of consumers who actually understand the
consumer credit business and who want to use credit is generally
speaking not very big, the amount of potential consumer credit
business is considerable, Huang noted.
</P>
<P>
He said that, after 20 years of rapid development, China has
sufficient material supplies and a solid foundation for consumer
credit. In addition, the income of consumers and the ability of
financial institutions to offer funds can meet the needs of
consumer credit development.
</P>
<P>
According to him, consumer credit is an important way to
stimulate consumer spending and can help promote economic
development by expanding purchasing power. It can also help
improve banks' assets, minimize financial risks, and promote the
establishment of a social credit system.
</P>
<P>
However, he pointed out, there are still many restrictions to
developing consumer credit, both socially and economically, and
central government departments concerned should design necessary
policies to improve social conditions for consumer credit.
</P>
</TEXT>
