<HEADLINE> China Becomes Major Stone Materials Producer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- China is now second only to Italy
in stone materials production with an annual output of more than
100 million sq.m. of granite, marble, terrazzo and other materials.
</P>
<P>
According to the China Chamber of International Commerce,
China's stone materials production has been growing at an average
annual rate of 30 percent over the past 15 years. With the world's
largest amount of stone reserves and greatest variety, China has a
large number of stone quarries in the provinces of Guangdong,
Fujian, Sichuan, Shandong, Zhejiang, Hunan, Hubei, Guizhou, and
Yunnan.
</P>
<P>
China is well-known internationally for its granite, marble,
and white marble production, and has markets for its stone
products in Japan, the Republic of Korea, Germany, the United
States, Russia, Thailand, Indonesia, Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhang Wenbo, deputy director of the China Stone
Materials Industry Association, China has made great headway in
expanding cooperation with overseas partners by setting up at
least 400 foreign-funded stone materials production ventures.
</P>
<P>
China has made progress in improving its stone materials
production technology, he said.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the country has introduced equipment from
Italy, Germany, and other countries that has helped the
development of its stone materials production.
</P>
<P>
China has over 100 equipment manufacturing enterprises for
stone production and exports such equipment to Russia, Kazakhstan,
Pakistan, Indonesia and Hungary, the official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
