<HEADLINE> Chinese Interior Decoration Sees Robust Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua)-- China's interior decoration industry
enjoys great market potential as more Chinese households choose to
remodel their homes, reported the Business Weekly of the China
Daily recently.
</P>
<P>
The paper cited a report from the China Social Survey Institute
as saying that Chinese families' spending on remodeling totals at
least 50 billion yuan (six billion US dollars) last year.
</P>
<P>
About one-fifth of residential housing in large and medium-
sized Chinese cities have been remodeled, according to the survey,
which questioned 876 families.
</P>
<P>
The average spending on remodeling was 87,000 yuan (10,500 US
dollars). The highest spending was 178,000 yuan (21,500 US dollars)
.
</P>
<P>
The report said that China's fast growing economy will further
fatten up the people's pockets, igniting bigger consumption for
interior decoration. 
</P>
