<HEADLINE> New York Beats Atlanta 90-78 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 23 (Xinhua) -- The New York Knicks used another
strong effort by their bench for a 90-78 victory over the Atlanta
Hawks and got a commanding lead in their Eastern Conference
semifinal series Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Chris Dudley scored 10 points in the fourth quarter and grabbed
12 rebounds and helped limit Hawks center Dikembe Mutombo to seven
points as he was part of another strong defensive performance.
</P>
<P>
After allowing Steve Smith to score 17 points in the first half,
the Knicks held him scoreless in the second half. Atlanta had only
11 points in the third quarter and was stuck in the 70s for the
second straight game.
</P>
<P>
Allan Houston and Latrell Sprewell scored 17 points apiece for
the eighth-seeded Knicks, who hold a 3-0 lead and can advance to
the conference finals for the first time since 1994 with another
win at home on Monday. Since the playoffs expanded to 16 teams in
1984, no No. 8 seed team has won two playoff series.
</P>
<P>
Grant Long scored 17 points for the Hawks, who shot just 31
percent (27-of-87) from the field and fell to 0-3 on the road in
the postseason. Atlanta will probably become the only pre-existing
team that has failed to reach the conference finals since the NBA
split into conferences in 1970.
</P>
<P>
No NBA team has won a best-of-seven series after losing the
first three games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
