<DOCNO> XIE19990524.0215 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> AC Milan Clinches League Title with 2-1 Win </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 23 (Xinhua) -- AC Milan narrowly beat Perugia 2-1 in
the last round of the Serie A soccer tournament on Sunday to claim
their 16th league title.
</P>
<P>
Their only challengers Lazio's same score win over Parma was
rendered irrelevant by Milan's away victory. Lazio finished
runners-up just one point behind the new league champions.
</P>
<P>
Argentine Andres Gulielminpietro put the visitors ahead in the
11th minute and twenty minutes later German Oliver Bierhoff scored
his 18th goal of the season to double the lead for AC Milan.
</P>
<P>
Japanese Hidetoshi Nakata netted in a 34th-minute penalty for
Perugia after a foul on his teammate Milan Rapaic, but AC Milan
rarely looked in trouble.
</P>
<P>
AC Milan, Lazio, Fiorentina, who drew 1-1 at Cagliari, and
Parma will represent Italy in the Champions' League next season.
</P>
<P>
Roma and Juventus qualified for UEFA Cup places. Italy's third
and final UEFA Cup berth will be decided in another play-off
between Bologna and Inter Milan.
</P>
<P>
Udinese's Brazilian striker Marcio Amoroso made it a double on
Sunday to take his season's tally to 21 and finish as joint top
goal scorer alongside Fiorentina's Argentine forward Gabriel
Batistuta.
</P>
<P>
At the bottom of the table, Salernitana were relegated despite
forcing a 1-1 draw at Piacenza. They will join Empoli, Sampdoria
and Vicenza in Serie B next season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
