<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Expert Predicts Stable Real Estate Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 24 (Xinhua) -- China's real estate market is to
remain stable in the remaining months of this year, says Ouyang
Yonghua of the China Real Estate Index System Office.
</P>
<P>
"The steady growth of urban residents' income stemming from the
country's excellent economic performance has created favorable
conditions for real estate investment and consumption," today's
China Daily quotes Ouyang as saying.
</P>
<P>
According to sources from the State Statistics Bureau, the
average per capita income of urban residents stood at 1,632 yuan (
197 U.S. dollars) in the first quarter of this year, up eight
percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The implementation of the Regulation on the Public Housing Fund
and the Regulation on Economy Housing Loan Management has also
helped improve housing credit policies, according to Ouyang.
</P>
<P>
He says that economy housing construction will not pose a
threat to the commercial housing market, because commercial
housing has its own characteristics in terms of location and
public facilities.
</P>
<P>
China invested 41.3 billion yuan (4.98 billion U.S. dollars) in
the first quarter of this year, with the amount of land allocated
for real estate development rising 93 percent to 7.42 million
square meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
