<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tube Babies Born in North China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Two couples with sterility problems
in north China's Shanxi Province have recently given birth to
healthy babies thanks to the help of IUI (inner uterus
insemination), an advanced medical technology.
</P>
<P>
The IUI technology in Shanxi is relatively backward compared
with other Chinese provinces, and prior to these two couples, the
province had reported no successful incidence of artificial
insemination.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yiding, a medical expert from the Second People's Hospital
in this capital of Shanxi, has conducted technological research in
the field for more than two year, and she has developed a new
treatment combining Chinese traditional and Western medical
technology, which has increased the IUI success rate in the
province to 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
A third woman who received this IUI treatment is expected to
give birth at the end of this month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
