<HEADLINE> Guangdong Builds Large Zoo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, May 24 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong Province is
building another large zoo in Jiedong County, east of the province.
</P>
<P>
Aimed at protecting rare species of animals and maintaining an
ecological balance, the zoo is expected to be completed next year
and will be home to more than 10,000 animals of over 300 species.
</P>
<P>
The zoo, with a planned investment of 500 million yuan, will
cover an area of 200 hectares and is only 18 kilometers away from
the city of Shantou, one of China's five largest economic
development zones. 
