<HEADLINE> Kankkunen Leads Argentine Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Finland's Juha Kankkunen led
the Rally of Argentina after Sunday's first leg of the race, the
seventh round of the World Championship.
</P>
<P>
After eight special stages the Subaru driver led Briton Richard
Burns with Frenchman Didier Auriol third in a Toyota.
</P>
<P>
Scotland's Colin McRae withdrew earlier after a crash incident
in the third special stage of the day. 
</P>
